function findFarmland(land) {
    const m = land.length, n = land[0].length;
    const res = [];

    for (let i = 0; i < m; ++i) {
        for (let j = 0; j < n; ++j) {
            if (land[i][j] === 1) {
                let r = i, c = j;
                while (r < m && land[r][j] === 1) ++r;
                while (c < n && land[i][c] === 1) ++c;
                for (let x = i; x < r; ++x) {
                    for (let y = j; y < c; ++y) {
                        land[x][y] = 0;
                    }
                }
                res.push([i, j, r - 1, c - 1]);
            }
        }
    }

    return res;
}
```


    1. Iterate over each cell (i, j) in the given land matrix.
2. If the cell value is 1 (farmland), initiate two pointers (r and c) at the current cell.
3. Move r downwards while the cells in the same column have value 1.
4. Move c rightwards while the cells in the same row have value 1.
5. Set all cells within the rectangle (i, j, r-1, c-1) to 0, and add [i, j, r-1, c-1] to the result list.
6. Repeat steps 1-5 for each cell in the land matrix.
7. Return the result list with coordinates for each group of farmland.

